1/\sin x
f(x)
t
t=\tan(x/2)
\sin x=\frac{2t}{1+t^2}
dx=\frac{2\,dt}{1+t^2}
\frac{dx}{\sin x}=\frac{dt}{t}=\ln(|t|)+C.
\int\csc x\ dx=\int\frac{\csc x(\csc x-\cot x)}{\csc x-\cot x}\ dx=\int\frac{-\csc x\cot x+\csc^2 x}{\csc x-\cot x}\ dx=\ln |\csc x-\cot x|+c
\sin 2y=\frac{2\tan y}{1+\tan^2y}=\frac{2\tan y}{\sec^2y}
\tan \frac x2=z\implies \frac12 \sec^2\frac x2 dx=dz
C
\int\frac{dx}{\sin x}=\int \frac{(\sec^2\frac x2) dx}{2\tan \frac x2}=\ln\left| \tan \frac x2\right|+C
